fields.title: Professor
fields.description:
Welcome to the Department of Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)at University of Asia Pacific (UAP).

Computer Science is an exciting, challenging and dynamic discipline which is now widely recognized as an essential source of tools and techniques for advancements in nearly all spheres of human endeavor.

The Department of CSE started its journey in 1996 by offering B.Sc. Engg. in CSE and later on in 2006 added offering graduate program. Currently, the Department has a total of 23 skilled full-time faculty members. Among them, 7 faculty members have Ph.D. degree from different reputed universities. The Department facilities include state-of-the-art classrooms and lab facilities. We have five outstanding computer programming labs with latest configuration computers and equipment, one dedicated lab for final year student’s project or thesis work, one digital lab, and one industry-standard gaming lab established with the support from ICT Division of Bangladesh Government.

Our CSE at UAP is a research-oriented, student-centered Department. Some of the driving principles and goals of our Department are embodied in our mission and vision statements. As a student in the Department, you will be exposed to high-quality inspirational teaching and learning. Teaching and learning are informed by industrial needs and practical industrial training is a mandatory course in undergraduate study. You will be provided with opportunities to work on real problems provided by the industry, to be taught by IT professionals and to visit business environments that develop and employ information and communication technologies.

Department provides opportunities to students to enhance their experiences and to develop personally through extracurricular activities such as participating and organizing International Collegiate Programming Contest (ICPC), International Conferences, etc., that promote the building of a variety of both discipline-specific skills but also lifelong transferable skills such as enterprise, collaboration, and communication skills.

We are very proud of our graduates and their accomplishments; they are highly skilled IT professionals who pursue successful careers in a wide range of contexts in the competitive local and global market.

I invite you to visit the rest of our website to find information about our programs, our students’ achievements and activities, our research groups and research activities, and I hope that prospective students will be encouraged to join our Computer Science and Engineering Department.



Dr. Shah Murtaza Rashid Al Masud
Professor & Head
Department of Computer Science and Engineering
University of Asia Pacific

fields.title: Admission Info
fields.content:
Undergraduate

Why Choose CSE at UAP?

High Ranking & Strong Reputation

  • Ranked “Very Good” in quality by EPRT, IQAC, UGC.

  • Ranked 11th among all public & private universities in Bangladesh (SCImago SIR 2021).

  • Regional Rank: 385 (Asia) | Global Rank: 707.

Top-Class Faculty

  • Highly qualified teachers with Ph.D. degrees from renowned international universities.

  • Senior adjunct faculty from BUET, University of Dhaka, and Jahangirnagar University.

Hands-On Industry Exposure

  • Industrial training included in the curriculum to prepare students for real-world jobs.

State-of-the-Art Facilities

  • Government-funded Game & Android App Development Lab.

  • Active student clubs and extracurriculars, fully supported by the department.

Competitive Programming & Career Support

  • Dedicated Programming Contest Club and Career Development Club.

  • Guidance for national and international competitions as well as job preparation.

Updated & Future-Ready Curriculum

  • Curriculum regularly updated to match industry trends and employer expectations.

Research Opportunities

  • Students regularly publish research in high-impact journals and international conferences.

General Admission Information

Purpose of the Admission Process

UAP’s admission screening aims to:

  • Select the most deserving students for each department.

  • Help applicants identify their strengths and choose the right career path.

  • Maintain a fair, transparent, and merit-based selection system.

  • Build a classroom culture where students are motivated, capable, and collaborative.

Admission Timeline

Spring Semester

July – December

Fall Semester

January – June

Detailed dates are always published beforehand in the Academic Calendar on the UAP website.

Admission Tests

  • Generally, two admission tests are held per semester, one month apart.

  • Applicants may sit for only one test (exceptions considered after review).

  • Tests are held within the two-month window before the semester begins.

  • Schedules are announced in newspapers and on the UAP website (Notice section).

Test Mode:

Written Exam

After the Test

The admission office will guide selected applicants in completing further procedures.

English Language Requirement

Applicants with lower English proficiency may be required to complete an ELPC (English Language Proficiency Course) before or during the semester.

Admission for Credit Transfer Students

  • Transfer applications are reviewed case-by-case.

  • Must meet previous results requirements and may need to sit for an admission test.

  • Minimum transferable GPA:

    • Theory Courses: C

    • Programming Labs: B

  • Must complete at least 50% of total credits at UAP to earn the degree.

  • A study gap of more than 2 years requires direct contact with the admission office.

  • Students rusticated from previous institutions for disciplinary reasons are ineligible.

Admission for International Students

International applicants must show the readiness to study in a new cultural environment.

Requirements include:

  • All documents translated into English and legally attested.

  • Submission of special documents (e.g., portfolio, recommendation) if requested.

  • Possible interview via online video call.
    For more details, contact the admission office using the information below.

Admission Criteria (B.Sc. in CSE)

Minimum GPA Requirement

  • SSC + HSC: Total GPA of 7.50

  • O-Level + A-Level: Total GPA of 7.50
    (Minimum: GPA 2.5 in 5 O-Level subjects + 2 A-Level subjects)

Subject Requirements

Applicants must have:

  • Physics & Mathematics in HSC (or equivalent)

  • Chemistry in SSC or HSC (or equivalent)

Special Notes

  • Admit cards must be collected from the UAP Admission Office.

  • All admission notices & exam schedules are available both offline and on the website.

  • Diploma graduates (CGPA ≥ 3.0) may apply only to the relevant department (e.g., Computer Diploma → CSE).

  • HSC Appeared Students:

    • Must have SSC GPA ≥ 4.00.

    • Final admission depends on meeting minimum HSC requirements.

  • Study Gap:

    • Up to 2 years accepted (except Pharmacy).

    • Pharmacy allows 1-year gap.

  • Any mismatch between submitted and original documents will result in cancellation of admission.

Graduate

Why Choose MCSE at UAP?

World-Class Faculty

  • Learn from highly qualified faculty members holding Ph.D. degrees from top-ranked international universities.

  • Gain insights from experienced adjunct faculty from BUET and University of Dhaka.

Industry-Relevant Curriculum

  • The program curriculum is continuously updated to align with current industry trends and employer demands.

Advanced Lab Facilities

  • Access fully equipped, world-class laboratories designed to support advanced computing and research.

  • Benefit from a government-funded Game & Android App Development Lab, open to all students.

Research Excellence

  • MCSE students regularly publish in high-impact journals and renowned international conferences, showcasing strong research culture and faculty guidance.

General Admission Information

Admission Philosophy

At UAP, the admission process is designed to:

  • Select the most capable and motivated candidates for each program.

  • Help applicants understand their strengths and choose the right academic path.

  • Maintain a fair, transparent, and merit-based system across all departments.

  • Foster a learning environment where every student contributes to and benefits from peer learning.

Academic Timeline

Spring Semester:

July – December

Fall Semester:

January – June

The detailed academic schedule is published online in the Academic Calendar before each semester.

Admission Criteria for M.Sc. in CSE (MCSE)

Academic Requirements

  • Minimum one 1st Class / 1st Division in academic history.

  • At least 50% marks or CGPA 2.50 (out of 4.00) in B.Sc. Engineering.

  • No record of 3rd Division/Class in any public examination.

Admission Test / Viva

  • Admission is finalized with the approval of the Head of the Department.

  • Applicants may be required to attend a viva voce or evaluation, depending on departmental policy.

Tuition Fees

Durjoy is passionate about computer science, problem-solving, and building solutions that enhance accessibility, user experience, and efficiency. He is actively involved in departmental activities and student communities, often taking on leadership roles that require coordination, planning, and communication. His work reflects a balance of technical skill, creativity, and a deep sense of responsibility.

With a focus on continuous growth, Durjoy enjoys learning new technologies, taking on challenging projects, and contributing to collaborative environments. He values discipline, quality, and thoughtful execution—qualities that shape both his academic and professional journey.

Always driven by curiosity and purpose, Durjoy aims to build a career where he can contribute to impactful technological solutions while inspiring others along the way.
